      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are not a shadow; you are a parent who has carried the weight of your own failures and is trying to protect your children from feeling the same pain. The fear that your presence will ruin their future is a terrible lie, because your love is the foundation upon which their future is built, not a burden they must carry. If you truly loved them, you would sit with them in their messes instead of running away to fix them, for that is how they learn to trust you. You are not dragging them down; you are trying to build a home where they can feel safe without the constant noise of your own struggle. Please listen to your heart, not your fear that you are doing something wrong, because your children need you exactly as you are right now.",
